02_Hiding_Text_in_Image
Aim: Hide and extract a text file inside an image file.
Procedure (Hiding):
Place "A.txt" (text) and "B.jpg" (image) on the desktop.

Open Command Prompt and navigate to the desktop.

Run: copy /b B.jpg + A.txt C.jpg to create "C.jpg".
Retrieval:

Open "C.jpg" with Notepad; the hidden text appears at the end.
Result: Successfully hid and extracted text within an image.
